a^2+b^2+c^2=(a+b+c)^2
\frac1a+\frac1b+\frac1c=0
(a+b+c)^2 = a^2 + b^2 + c^2 + 2ab + 2ac + 2bc.
\frac{1}{a}+\frac{1}{b} + \frac{1}{c} = 0
\frac{ab+ac+bc}{abc} = 0.
ab+ac+bc = 0
